i |= 1 << j  // sets bit j
i &= ~(1 << j) // clears bit j
i & 1 << j // tests bit j

C operator precedence

1. postfix operators (left to right associative)
[] array subscripting
() function call
. structure[union] member
-> structure[union] memeber from pointer
++, -- increment or decrement(postfix)

2. prefix operators(right to left associative)
++, -- increment or decrement(prefix)
& address
* indirection
+, - unary plus or minus
~ bitwise complement
! logical negation
sizeof sizeof operator

---------------------------------------------------
3. cast
() parentheses
---------------------------------------------------

4. multiplicative
*, /, % 

5. additive
+, -
---------------------------------------------------

6. bitwise shift
>> <<
---------------------------------------------------

7. relation
<, >, <=, >=

8. equality
==, !=

---------------------------------------------------
9. & 10. ^ 11. |
---------------------------------------------------
12. && 13. ||
---------------------------------------------------
14. ? :
---------------------------------------------------
15. assignment
=, +=, -=, *=, /=, &=, ^=, |=, <<=, >>=
---------------------------------------------------
16. , comma





